<author><name><![CDATA[Tenzen]]></name></author>
<updated>2014-02-20T23:41:06-07:00</updated>
<published>2014-02-20T23:41:06-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=332&amp;p=11086#p11086</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=332&amp;p=11086#p11086"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Add Multiple Custom AgentRansack Searches to your Search]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=332&amp;p=11086#p11086"><![CDATA[
Well, I use FileLocatorPro, but on my laptop I have AgentRansack Portable Version, and in the Search Syntax it requires an extra Semi-colon to work properly<br /><br />for example, instead of: <br /><br />FileLocatorPro.exe -f %1 -r -s -d &quot;C:\;D:\;E:\&quot;<br /><br />You need to type:<br /><br />D:\My Portable Programs\Agent Ransack\AgentRansack.exe -f %1 -r -s -d &quot;C:\;D:\;E:\;&quot;<br /><br />Note the extra Semi-Colon at the end of the string, before the close-quotes<br /><br />So, I dont know if thats just the difference between AgentRansack &amp; FileLocatorPro, or if its just the way the Portable Version of AgentRansack works.. but there it is, if anyone else was having trouble<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=359">Tenzen</a> — Thu Feb 20, 2014 11:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
